Fifth Grade Metal Repousse

   Posted on February 7, 2013 by Wilder Paint Splatters
   Reply


   metal2


   Fifth Grade created these mixed media projects using metal tooling foil
   and metallic markers on black paper for the mat.  Students had to use
   components of composition and good design in the planning stages.
   Metal repousse and chasing  is a metalworking technique in which the
   metal is  shaped by using tools from the top and reverse side to create
   a design in low relief. The students were encouraged to create a lot of
   texture in their piece.

   metal

