Cool Days, Warm Hands

   Posted on February 7, 2013 by Wilder Paint Splatters
   Reply

   mitten

   Kindergarten has been working on using pattern in an artwork and
   learning warm and cool colors.  The result?  Warm colored mittens
   covered in a zentangle-ish pattern and backgrounds painted in cool
   colors, using plastic wrap to create an icy texture.

   Enjoy these paintings by Hallie and Zach.

   mitten1

   mitten2

